# .env.example
# This file contains environment variables and helpful command notes.

# ==============================================================================
# codebase-memory-mcp (Codebase Brain) Commands & Notes
# ==============================================================================
# The codebase-memory-mcp is an MCP server that maintains a knowledge graph of 
# this repository, enabling structural search and exploration.
#
# 1. Launch the 3D Graph UI:
#    codebase-memory-mcp --ui=true --port=9749
#    (Open http://localhost:9749 in your browser after running this)
#
# 2. Manually Re-index the Repository:
#    codebase-memory-mcp cli index_repository '{"repo_path": "'$PWD'"}'
#    (Replace $PWD with the absolute path if not running from the project root)
#
# 3. Enable Auto-indexing on Session Start:
#    codebase-memory-mcp config set auto_index true
#
# 4. Search the graph from CLI (example):
#    codebase-memory-mcp cli search_graph '{"name_pattern": ".*Roadmap.*"}'
# ==============================================================================
